Syntax
public sealed class XmlResults : IEnumerator, ICollection, IEnumerable
Remarks

XmlResults is a collection of XmlValue objects, which may represent any one of the supported types. An XmlResults object is created by executing a query or calling Execute(QueryContext).

There are several ways that a query is performed. One is to call Query(String, QueryContext, QueryOptions) directly. This mechanism is appropriate for one-shot queries that will not be repeated.

A second approach is to create an XQueryExpression using Prepare(String, QueryContext). You then execute the query expression using Execute(QueryContext). This approach is appropriate for queries that will be performed more than once as it means that the expense of compiling the query can be amortized across multiple queries.

Note that when you perform a query, you must provide an QueryContext object. Using this object, you can indicate whether you want the query to be performed eagerly or lazily. If eager evaluation is specified (the default), then the resultant values are stored within the XmlResults object. If lazy evaluation is selected, then the resultant values will be computed as needed. In this case the XmlResults object will maintain a reference to the affected containers (Container), query context (QueryContext), and expression (XQueryExpression).

The XmlResults class provides an iteration interface through the NextDocument() and NextValue() methods. These methods return null when no more results are available (IsNull() returns true). Reset() can be called to reset the iterator, and the subsequent call to NextDocument() or NextValue() will return the first value of the result set.

Reset()

Resets the result set iterator.

Declaration
public void Reset()
Remarks

If a query was processed with eager evaluation, a call to the Reset() method resets the result set iterator, so that a subsequent call to NextDocument() or NextValue() methods will return the first value in the result set. If the query was processed with lazy evaluation, then a call to the Reset() method throws an exception.
